00:09:21.530 --> 00:09:23.930
Bonus Fact:

00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:28.410
As noted, the Pure Food and Drug Act of 1906,
still left an amazing amount of leeway to

00:09:28.410 --> 00:09:32.310
poison people to save a buck without any real
consequences.

00:09:32.310 --> 00:09:35.060
This leads us to the Elixir Sulfanilamide
Incident.

00:09:35.060 --> 00:09:40.040
In a nutshell, sulfanilamide is actually a
perfectly safe antibiotic when administered

00:09:40.040 --> 00:09:45.200
properly, and was used, among other things,
at the time to good effect at treating streptococcal

00:09:45.200 --> 00:09:46.200
infections.

00:09:46.200 --> 00:09:50.200
However, in an attempt to create a liquid
version of the drug (it normally came in either

00:09:50.200 --> 00:09:53.140
powder or tablet form), the lead chemist at
S.E.

00:09:53.140 --> 00:09:58.570
Massengill Company, Harold Cole Watkins, mixed
it with diethylene glycol, commonly used today

00:09:58.570 --> 00:10:00.710
in antifreeze and as a solvent.

00:10:00.710 --> 00:10:05.350
At the time, it was known that diethylene
glycol was highly poisonous to humans (most

00:10:05.350 --> 00:10:09.920
notably causing kidney failure), but Watkins
did not know this when he decided to use it

00:10:09.920 --> 00:10:10.920
in the company’s elixir.

00:10:10.920 --> 00:10:14.480
He chose it owing to how well sulfanilamide
dissolved in the substance and because diethylene

00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:18.990
glycol tastes slightly sweet, making it particularly
good for getting children to take their medicine.

00:10:18.990 --> 00:10:23.140
In this case, even animal testing would not
have been required to discover the substance

00:10:23.140 --> 00:10:24.180
was toxic.

00:10:24.180 --> 00:10:28.150
Watkins would have merely needed to do a surface
level look into the compound, with several

00:10:28.150 --> 00:10:32.840
previous published studies noting diethylene
glycol, even in relatively small doses, would

00:10:32.840 --> 00:10:35.790
cause kidney damage and potentially failure
of said organ.

00:10:35.790 --> 00:10:39.190
But no such due-diligence research nor testing
to determine the safety of such an elixir

00:10:39.190 --> 00:10:42.510
before putting it on the market was required
at the time.

00:10:42.510 --> 00:10:46.290
Blissfully unaware that they were about to
start selling a tasty tonic of death to their

00:10:46.290 --> 00:10:47.400
customers, S.E.

00:10:47.400 --> 00:10:52.990
Massengill sent out 633 shipments of the elixir
in the autumn of 1937 to pharmacists across

00:10:52.990 --> 00:10:53.990
the nation.

00:10:53.990 --> 00:10:57.760
It didn’t take long for disturbing reports
to begin coming in, including news of deaths

00:10:57.760 --> 00:10:59.490
trickling back to S.E.

00:10:59.490 --> 00:11:04.220
Massengill Co, resulting in them issuing telegrams
requesting the elixir be sent back for a full

00:11:04.220 --> 00:11:08.440
refund, though not disclosing to pharmacists
the seriousness of the issue if they ignored

00:11:08.440 --> 00:11:09.440
the telegram.

00:11:09.440 --> 00:11:13.340
This all was capped by a short and truly heart
wrenching letter by one Marie Nidiffer to

00:11:13.340 --> 00:11:17.230
President Franklin D. Roosevelt describing
what happened in the days following administering

00:11:17.230 --> 00:11:21.810
the drug to her 6 year old daughter, who at
the time was suffering from a sore throat:

00:11:21.810 --> 00:11:25.900
The first time I ever had occasion to call
in a doctor for [Joan] and she was given Elixir

00:11:25.900 --> 00:11:27.160
of Sulfanilamide.

00:11:27.160 --> 00:11:31.710
All that is left to us is the caring for her
little grave.

00:11:31.710 --> 00:11:36.080
Even the memory of her is mixed with sorrow
for we can see her little body tossing to

00:11:36.080 --> 00:11:40.820
and fro and hear that little voice screaming
with pain and it seems as though it would

00:11:40.820 --> 00:11:42.030
drive me insane.

00:11:42.030 --> 00:11:46.230
… It is my plea that you will take steps
to prevent such sales of drugs that will take

00:11:46.230 --> 00:11:51.740
little lives and leave such suffering behind
and such a bleak outlook on the future as

00:11:51.740 --> 00:11:52.840
I have tonight.

00:11:52.840 --> 00:11:55.560
As for Dr. Samual Evans Massengill, who owned
S.E.

00:11:55.560 --> 00:11:59.970
Massengill Co., he responded to the many dozens
of deaths caused by his company’s negligence

00:11:59.970 --> 00:12:01.950
by issuing the following statement:

00:12:01.950 --> 00:12:06.340
My chemists and I deeply regret the fatal
results, but there was no error in the manufacture

00:12:06.340 --> 00:12:07.340
of the product.

00:12:07.340 --> 00:12:11.450
We have been supplying a legitimate professional
demand and no one could have foreseen the

00:12:11.450 --> 00:12:12.770
unlooked-for results.

00:12:12.770 --> 00:12:16.350
I do not feel that there was any responsibility
on our part…

00:12:16.350 --> 00:12:20.210
Needless to say, when all this came to light,
the public were more than a little outraged,

00:12:20.210 --> 00:12:21.210
with S.E.

00:12:21.210 --> 00:12:24.730
Massengill’s somewhat brazen statement that
his drug company wasn’t responsible for

00:12:24.730 --> 00:12:29.160
making sure their products weren’t simply
poison at the recommended dose before selling

00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:30.160
them.

00:12:30.160 --> 00:12:34.340
To add to the tragedy, it appears Harold Watkins
did not quite have the clear conscience of

00:12:34.340 --> 00:12:38.830
Dr. Massengill, with Watkins sadly committing
suicide not long after it came to light that

00:12:38.830 --> 00:12:42.040
his error had resulted in the deaths of over
100 people.

00:12:42.040 --> 00:12:46.820
In the end, the Elixir Sulfanilamide Incident
was the final straw, spurring an upgraded

00:12:46.820 --> 00:12:51.530
to the Pure Food and Drug Act of 1906 in the
form of the 1938 Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic

00:12:51.530 --> 00:12:54.890
Act to hopefully prevent such a tragedy from
occurring again.

00:12:54.890 --> 00:12:58.340
Among other things, the Act required that
for the first time in US history, drug makers

00:12:58.340 --> 00:13:02.720
had to demonstrate to the FDA that drugs were
reasonably safe before they could be marketed

00:13:02.720 --> 00:13:07.130
to the public, set standards for how different
kinds of food should look and be packaged,

00:13:07.130 --> 00:13:10.980
and specified legal maximums for “certain
poisonous substances” commonly added to

00:13:10.980 --> 00:13:19.230
food and drink at the time.

